article.headline: Sears scores 22, UT Martin defeats Tennessee Tech 81-73
article.description: — Jordan Sears had 22 points in UT Martin's 81-73 victory over Tennessee Tech on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Sears scores 22, UT Martin defeats Tennessee Tech 81-73
article.story: COOKEVILLE, Tenn. -- — Jordan Sears had 22 points in UT Martin's 81-73 victory over Tennessee Tech on Saturday night. Sears had six rebounds and six assists for the Skyhawks (9-6, 2-0 Ohio Valley Conference). Jacob Crews scored 17 points, going 6 of 10 (5 for 8 from 3-point range). KK Curry shot 4 for 9 (1 for 4 from 3-point range) and 7 of 9 from the free-throw line to finish with 16 points. Jayvis Harvey finished with 22 points for the Golden Eagles (5-10, 0-2). Diante Wood added 18 points for Tennessee Tech. Rodney Johnson Jr. also recorded 13 points, six rebounds and four blocks. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
